properties.text: Spice Girls: Britain was ready to spice up its life with Sporty, Scary, Baby, Ginger and Posh. The female five-some successfully held pop domination in the 90s, selling over 85 million records worldwide.

Harry Potter: The story of the boy wizard has captured the attention of children and adults across the globe. Over 450 million copies have been sold worldwide, making it the best-selling book series in history.

The 90s saw a resurgence in Britain's self confidence. It was the decade of 'Cool Britannia' as the UK's music, fashion and art took the world by storm. Britain voted in New Labour as Oasis and Blur blared on the radio. Amid the upheaval of the Gulf War, the dotcom boom, and the death of Princess Diana, Britons looked ahead towards a new millennium.

The Internet: Tim Berners-Lee debuted his system that made it easier to share data between scientists. His project would make the Internet accessible to the masses, and by the end of the decade more than 100m people were accessing the web.
